llppsshhuutt -- Command

Turn off the printer daemon despooler
llppsshhuutt [-dd]

The command llppsshhuutt turns off the printer daemon llppsscchheedd.

The option -dd  tells llppsshhuutt to finish the jobs  that are currently printing
before it  shuts down the daemon.  If jobs  are interrupted while printing,
the printer daemon llppsscchheedd reprints them when it restarts.

